		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=126408"><span id=Sage>Bikamar</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>307 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.66]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Bikamar&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Initially, go for AC ... it will keep you up longer at lower levels when your healers mana pool isn't so great.<br><br>Once you start grouping with clerics with Complete Heal (mid 30s this will start happening I think), start changing from AC to STA/HPs.<br><br>Other stats will rise naturally as you improve your gear.<br><br>STR is good for a little extra damage each successful attack you make.<br><br>DEX is good for procs and therefore agro at higher levels (you need big jumps in dex to see a difference, like 25 odd in my experience ie 125, 150, 175 so on).<br><br>STA/HPs = more efficient CHs from your cleric (and druid/shammy incomplete heals when you get there) = more time fighting and less time regening mana.<br><br>AGI makes a very small difference to AC (damage avoidance) ... naturally yours is above 80 so don't worry about it.<br><br>INT/WIS/CHA ... bah, who cares? joking.&nbsp;&nbsp;INT/WIS good for tradeskills ... CHA handy for keeping day-to-day costs down, but once it's above 120, it makes no difference.<br><br>Search back through this forum for some excellent posts on stats ... Annheiser, Kdsktan, Xaanru are some authors to look for.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>"...come back here ya coward! I'll bite yer kneecaps off..."<br><br>It's not the class that makes the player - it's the player that makes the class</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class